---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" description="Resume — Shrivathsa M S">
  <div class="resume-container">

    <a href="/resume.pdf" download class="download-link">Download PDF</a>

    <section>
      <h2>Skills</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="label">Programming Languages</td>
            <td>Python, TypeScript, JavaScript, Go, C++</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="label">Frontend</td>
            <td>React.js, Next.js, Redux, Webpack, Web Audio API</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="label">CSS & UI Libraries</td>
            <td>Tailwind CSS, Chakra UI, Material Design, SASS</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="label">Backend</td>
            <td>FastAPI, Node.js, Express.js, REST API Design, WebSockets, Microservices</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="label">Databases</td>
            <td>PostgreSQL, MongoDB, SQLite</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="label">Infra & Tools</td>
            <td>Docker, Linux, AWS (EC2, S3), Cloudflare R2, Railway, GitHub Actions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="label">Testing</td>
            <td>Jest, Cypress, Vitest, pytest</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="label">SDLC</td>
            <td>Agile, Git, Jira, Gerrit</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Experience</h2>

      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div>
            <h3>Solvendo <span class="org-desc">— Legal-tech startup</span></h3>
            <span class="role">Software Engineer</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meta">
            <span>Bengaluru, KA</span>
            <span>July 2023 – February 2025</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Built and shipped frontend features for a bankruptcy resolution platform used by institutions including Canara Bank and IBBI, handling complex multi-role workflows across banks, companies, and legal teams.</li>
          <li>Bootstrapped a new Next.js frontend from scratch, establishing coding standards and a reusable component library that the team built features on top of. <span class="tech">Next.js, Chakra UI, NextAuth.js</span></li>
          <li>Built a high-performance blockchain analytics dashboard with rich interactive time-series charts and a drag-and-drop analysis interface — sub-2s load time and a Lighthouse score of 93 at 10k MAU. <span class="tech">Next.js, React-DND, ApexCharts</span></li>
          <li>Diagnosed and resolved React performance bottlenecks using React DevTools and Lighthouse, cutting First Contentful Paint by 50%.</li>
          <li>Built a blockchain data aggregation microservice in Go using WebSockets and REST endpoints, achieving 8x higher throughput than the previous solution. <span class="tech">Go, net/http, WebSockets</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div>
            <h3>Indian Institute of Science</h3>
            <span class="role">Research Engineer</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meta">
            <span>Bengaluru, KA</span>
            <span>January 2023 – July 2023</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Engineered multi-agent robot systems for agricultural applications, achieving 2x improvement in obstacle avoidance performance through novel algorithms. <span class="tech">Python, ROS, EGO Planner</span></li>
          <li>Developed motion planning and perception software for UAVs in Python. <span class="tech">ROS, Intel Realsense cameras, 2D Lidars</span></li>
          <li>Integrated UAVs with DJI control software using SDKs to enhance automation capabilities. <span class="tech">Python, DJI SDK</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div>
            <h3>NewSpace Research & Technologies <span class="org-desc">— UAV & robotics R&D company</span></h3>
            <span class="role">Robotics Engineer</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meta">
            <span>Bengaluru, KA</span>
            <span>October 2021 – January 2023</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Worked on ROS-based autonomy software for UAVs operating in GPS-denied environments. <span class="tech">ROS, Python, Linux, C++</span></li>
          <li>Optimized robot localization using visual SLAM and LiDAR SLAM algorithms in C++. <span class="tech">OpenCV, OpenSLAM, VINS-Stereo/Mono, Ouster Lidars</span></li>
          <li>Developed UAV simulation tools using Python and physics simulation software. <span class="tech">Python, Gazebo, Docker, C++</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Projects</h2>

      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div>
            <h3>CoheMix</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="project-desc">A mix comparison tool for audio engineers. Validates and processes uploaded audio server-side using ffprobe and threaded analysis, gain-matches tracks via integrated LUFS, and computes loudness, frequency, and spatial features. Frontend renders results through meters and graphs, as well as a live spectrum and goniometer via the Web Audio API. <span class="tech">Python, FastAPI, React, TypeScript, PostgreSQL, Cloudflare R2, Railway</span></p>
      </div>

      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div>
            <h3>BarFly Browser Extension</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="project-desc">A browser extension that replaces the bookmarks toolbar with an LRU-cached view of recently interacted bookmarks, keeping the most relevant links always accessible. <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/barfly/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Firefox store page</a>. <span class="tech">TypeScript, Firefox/Chrome Browser Extensions API</span></p>
      </div>

      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div>
            <h3>WikiTree Browser Extension</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="project-desc">A Chrome extension to visualize Wikipedia rabbit holes as interactive trees, built using TypeScript and React. <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/wikitree/gmepfbiaaamedihnliggicgbphigbcje?hl=en&pli=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chrome store page</a>. <span class="tech">TypeScript, React.js, Chrome Browser Extensions API</span></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <div class="entry">
        <div class="entry-header">
          <div>
            <h3>BMS College of Engineering</h3>
            <span class="role">Degree in Mechanical Engineering (BE)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meta">
            <span>Bengaluru, KA</span>
            <span>July 2017 – July 2021</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="edu-detail">Electives: AI, Java, Robotics &nbsp;·&nbsp; GPA: 8.75</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Publications</h2>
      <p class="publication">Kumar Ankit, Shrivathsa M S, Shishir Kolathaya, Debasish Ghose. "Reachability Analysis of UAVs through Cluttered Environments." <em>AIAA SciTech 2024 Forum</em>, January 2024. <a href="https://doi.org/10.2514/6.2024-2017" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">DOI: 10.2514/6.2024-2017</a></p>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .resume-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    max-width: 780px;
    width: 100%;
    padding-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .download-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 0.35rem 0.85rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }
  .download-link:hover {
    background-color: var(--accent);
    color: #000;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .org-desc {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    opacity: 0.55;
  }

  .entry {
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .entry:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .entry-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .role {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-end;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    opacity: 0.65;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .tech {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    opacity: 0.55;
  }

  table {
    border-collapse: collapse;
    width: 100%;
  }

  td {
    padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem 0.35rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  td.label {
    white-space: nowrap;
    opacity: 0.6;
    padding-right: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .edu-detail {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    opacity: 0.65;
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0 0;
  }

  .project-desc,
  .publication {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .project-desc a,
  .publication a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .project-desc a:hover,
  .publication a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline 2px var(--accent);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .entry-header {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
    .meta {
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
    td.label {
      display: block;
      padding-bottom: 0;
    }
    td {
      display: block;
    }
  }
</style>
